 China. This is a new, complete translation into English, with critical notes and introduction, and based on recent scholarship, of Yan Zhitui's Family Instructions, and of all of his extant literary works, including his self-annotated poetic autobiography and a never-before-translated fragmentary rhapsody, as well as of his biographies in dynastic histories.  afunded by The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4a. 4aBildung. 4aClan. 4aEthik. 4aFamilie. 4aLebensführung. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh  aFamily Instructions.  aYan Zhitui.  aclan and family.  aconduct of life.  aethics.1 aKroll, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt2 aThe Andrew W. Mellon Foundationefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97815015031390 cprintz978150151140040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501503191zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501503191zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/cover